children.text:
Let us worship the Lord God our Maker.
Let us kneel to the Lord our God;
for we are the sheep of His pasture,
He will guide us by His mighty hand.

Let us before His presence come
with praise and thankful voice;
let us sing psalms to Him with grace,
and make a joyful noise.

Exalt the Lord, His praise proclaim;
all you His servants, praise His Name,
who in the Lord's House always stand
and humbly serve at His command.
The Lord is good, His praise proclaim;
since it is pleasant, praise His Name;
His people for His own He takes
and His distinctive treasure makes.

I know the Lord is high in state,
above all gods our God is great;
the Lord performs what He decrees,
in heav'n and earth, in depths and seas.
He makes the moisture to ascend
in clouds from earth's remotest end;
the lightnings flash at His command;
He holds the cyclone in His hand.

Exalt the Lord, His praise proclaim;
all you His servants, praise His Name,
who in the Lord's House always stand
and humbly serve at His command.
Forever praise and bless His Name,
and in the church His praise proclaim;
in Zion is His dwelling place;
O praise the Lord, show forth His grace.

My heart is sure, O God,
a grateful song I sing;
awake, O harp, in joyful strains;
to praise my God and King.

Sing to God new songs of worship;
all His deeds are marvellous;
He has brought salvation to us
with His hand and holy arm.
He has shown to all the nations
righteousness and saving power;
He recalled His truth and mercy
to His people Israel.

Sing to God new songs of worship;
Earth has seen His victory;
let the lands on Earth be joyful
praising Him with thankfulness.
Sound upon the harp His praises,
play to Him with melody,
let the trumpets sound His triumph,
show your joy to God the King.

My words from You I cannot hide;
I feel Your power on every side;
such wondrous knowledge, aweful might,
unfathomed depth, unmeasured height!

God the Lord is King of glory,
Zion, tell the world His fame;
ancient Israel, the story
of His faithfulness proclaim:
He is holy; He is holy;
holy is His awesome Name.

Laws divine to them were spoken
from the pillar of the cloud;
sacred precepts, quickly broken!
Fiercely then His justice flowed:
He is holy; He is holy;
to the ground their hearts were bowed.

Truly You are not a God
who in evil takes delight;
evil shall not dwell with You;
nor the proud Your favour win.

For those in trouble and oppressed,
a source of strength is He;
for those who trust and seek the Lord,
a present help He'll be.

Forever settled in the heav'ns,
Your Word O Lord shall firmly stand;
Your faithfulness shall never fail;
the earth remains at Your command.

I would have perished in my woe
had not I loved Your law divine;
that law I never can forget;
O keep me, Lord, and Saviour mine.

All glory be to God
the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit;
from ages past it was,
is now, and evermore shall be.

The world is also firmly placed,
its steadfast place to hold;
for You are the eternal God,
Your throne is fixed of old.

This is my Father's world,
the birds their carols raise;
the morning light, the lily white,
declare their Maker's praise.
This is my Father's world;
why should my heart be sad?
The Lord is King, let the heavens ring;
God reigns, let the earth be glad!

To Him who chose us first,
before the world began;
to Him who bore the curse,
to save rebellious man;
to Him who formed our hearts anew,
is endless praise and glory due.

The Lord is King! Lift up your voice,
O earth, and all you heavens, rejoice;
from world to world the song shall ring:
The Lord omnipotent is King!

God reigns! He reigns with glory crowned:
let Christians make a joyful sound,
for Christ is at the Father's side:
the man of love, the crucified.

Praise the Lord for times and seasons,
cloud and sunshine, wind and rain;
spring to melt the snows of winter
till the waters flow again;
grass upon the mountain pastures,
golden valleys thick with grain.

He counts the number of the stars;
He names them every one.
Our Lord is great and great in power;
His wisdom search can none.

He gathered them from all the lands,
from north, south, east and west;
they'd wandered in the wilderness;
no city found to rest.

God be in my head, and in my understanding;
God be in my eyes, and in my looking;
God be in my mouth, and in my speaking;
God be in my heart, and in my thinking;
God be at my end, and at my departing.

We praise You, O God
for the Son of Your love,
for Jesus who died,
and has now gone above.

Revive us again;
fill each heart with Your love;
may each soul be rekindled
with fire from above.

His call we obey, like Abram of old,
not knowing our way, but faith makes us bold;
for though we are strangers, we have a good Guide,
and trust, in all dangers, the Lord will provide.

With grateful heart my thanks I bring,
before the great Your praise I sing;
I worship in Your holy place
and praise You for Your truth and grace;
for truth and grace together shine
in Your most holy Word divine.

You will stretch out Your mighty arm
to save me when my foes alarm;
the work You have for me begun
shall by Your grace be fully done.
Forever mercy dwells with You;
O Lord, my Maker, ever true.

Bless the Lord, all things created;
be His Holy Name adored
all throughout His wide dominion;
O my soul, bless now the Lord.

So may this bounteous God
through all our life be near us;
to fill our hearts with joy,
and with His peace to cheer us;
to keep us in His grace,
and guide us when perplexed;
to free us from all ills
in this world and the next.

Eternal Spirit, by whose breath
the soul is raised from sin and death;
before Your throne we sinners bend;
to us Your living power extend.

Glory to the King of angels,
glory to the church's King;
glory to the King of nations;
heaven and earth, your praises bring.
Glory, glory, glory, glory,
to the King of Glory bring!

Father, we adore You,
lay our lives before You;
how we love You!

Jesus, we adore You,
lay our lives before You;
how we love You!

Spirit, we adore You,
lay our lives before You;
how we love You!

Christ, at God's right hand victorious,
You will judge the world You made;
Lord, in mercy help Your servants
for whose freedom You have paid:
raise us up from dust to glory,
guard us from all sin today;
King enthroned above all praises,
save Your people, Lord, we pray.

My heart knows none above You;
for You I long, I thirst,
and know that, if I love You,
Lord, You have loved me first.

Whatever God ordains is right;
He never will deceive us.
He leads us by the proper path;
we know He will not leave us.
And take, content, what He has sent;
His hand can turn our griefs away,
and patiently we wait His day.

The thunders of His hand
keep all the world in awe;
His wrath and justice stand
to guard His holy law;
and where His love resolves to bless,
His truth confirms and seals the grace.

Sovereign grace o'er sin abounding,
ransomed souls, the tidings swell;
love so deep that knows no sounding;
who its breadth or length can tell?
On its glories, on its glories,
let my soul forever dwell.

Heirs of God, joint-heirs with Jesus,
long ere time its race begun;
to His Name eternal praises;
O what wonders He has done!
One with Jesus, one with Jesus,
by eternal union one.

Now your vows pay to Jehovah,
claim Him as your God alone;
let all bring their gifts before Him,
worship Him, all-holy One.
Mighty ones obey and fear Him,
rulers bow before His throne;
mighty ones obey and fear Him,
rulers bow before His throne.

O God, You are our King of old;
salvation You have wrought;
in safety through the mighty sea
our fathers You have brought.

Let not Your saints be put to shame;
no longer in Your sight
permit Your foes to shout their boasts;
Lord, vindicate the right.

He smiles, and my comforts abound;
His grace as the dew shall descend;
and walls of salvation surround
the soul He delights to defend.

You made him lord of all Your works;
beneath him all things be:
all sheep and cattle, and the beasts
that in the field do feed;

Praise the Lord, you heavens, adore Him;
praise Him, angels in the height;
sun and moon rejoice before Him;
praise Him, all you stars and light.

Worship, honour, power and blessing
You are worthy to receive;
loudest praises, without ceasing,
right it is for us to give.
Help us, bright angelic spirits;
joined with ours, your voices raise;
help to show our Saviour's merits,
help to sing Emmanuel's praise.

Come, lift your hearts on high:
Hallelujah! Amen!
Let praises fill the sky;
Hallelujah! Amen!
He is our guide and friend;
to us He'll condescend;
His love shall never end.
Hallelujah! Amen!

Let us praise, and join the chorus
of the saints enthroned on high;
here they trusted Him before us,
now their praises fill the sky:
'You have washed us with Your blood;
You are worthy, Lamb of God.'

Trust in Him, you saints, forever;
He is faithful, changing never;
neither force nor guile can sever
those He loves from Him.

My heart and voice I raise
to spread Messiah's praise;
Messiah's praise let all repeat;
the universal Lord,
by whose almighty Word
creation rose in form complete.

Jesus! - Name of all our praising
in this world to which You came;
here we sing of love amazing,
and Your saving power proclaim;
hearts and voices heavenward raising,
all our hope is in Your Name!

Our hope is in no other save in You;
our faith is built upon Your promise true;
Lord give us peace and make us calm and sure,
that in Your strength we evermore endure.

O grant that nothing in my soul
may dwell, but Your pure love alone;
O may Your love possess me whole,
my joy, my treasure, and my crown!
Strange flames far from my heart remove;
my every act, word, thought, be love.

Unwearied may I this pursue,
dauntless to the high prize aspire;
hourly within my soul renew
this holy flame, this heavenly fire;
and day and night be all my care
to guard the sacred treasure there.

In suffering, make Your love my peace;
in weakness, make Your love my power;
and, when the storms of life shall cease,
Jesus, in that tremendous hour,
in death, as life, Lord be my Guide,
and save me, who for me has died.

When He lived on earth among us,
friend of sinners was His name;
now, in glory far above us,
He rejoices in the same;
still He calls us brethren, friends,
and to all our needs attends.

Through the love of God our Saviour
all will be well.
Free and changeless is His favour,
all, all is well.
Precious is the blood that healed us;
perfect is the grace that sealed us;
strong the hand stretched forth to shield us;
all must be well.

O come, true Branch of Jesse, free
Your children from this tyranny;
from depths of hell Your people save,
to rise victorious from the grave:
Rejoice! Rejoice!
Emmanuel shall come to you, O Israel.

Tell out, my soul, the greatness of the Lord!
Unnumbered blessings give my spirit voice;
tender to me the promise of His Word;
in God my Saviour shall my heart rejoice.

Tell out, my soul, the greatness of His Name!
Make known His might, the deeds His arm has done;
His mercy sure, from age to age the same;
His Holy Name -- the Lord, the Mighty One.

Prophets foretold Him, infant of wonder;
angels behold Him on His throne;
worthy our Saviour of all their praises;
happy forever are His own.

Chorus
Christ the babe is Lord of all;
Christ the babe is Lord of all!

For He is our childhood's pattern:
day by day like us He grew;
He was little, weak and helpless;
tears and smiles like us He knew:
and He feels for all our sadness,
and He shares in all our gladness.

Hosanna in the highest!
That ancient song we sing;
for Christ is our Redeemer,
the Lord of heaven our King;
O may we ever praise Him,
with heart and life and voice,
and in His holy presence
eternally rejoice.

All those who fear Your Name
shall my companions be;
Your mercy fills the earth, O Lord;
Your statutes, Lord, teach me.

For that old rugged cross so despised by the world,
has a wondrous attraction for me;
for the dear Lamb of God left His glory above,
to bear it to dark Calvary.

In the old rugged cross, stained with blood so divine,
a wonderful beauty I see;
for on that rugged cross Jesus suffered and died,
to pardon and sanctify me.

There is a fountain filled with blood
drawn from Emmanuel's veins,
and sinners plunged beneath that flood
lose all their guilty stains;
lose all their guilty stains;
lose all their guilty stains;
and sinners plunged beneath that flood
lose all their guilty stains.

The dying thief rejoiced to see
that fountain in his day;
and there have I, as vile as he,
washed all my sins away;
washed all my sins away;
washed all my sins away;
and there have I, as vile as he,
washed all my sins away.

O Lamb of God, Your precious blood
shall never lose its power,
till all the ransomed church of God
is saved, to sin no more;
is saved, to sin no more;
is saved, to sin no more;
till all the ransomed church of God
is saved, to sin no more.

And since, by faith, I saw the stream
Your flowing wounds supply,
redeeming love has been my theme,
and shall be till I die;
and shall be till I die;
and shall be till I die;
redeeming love has been my theme,
and shall be till I die.

When this poor lisping stammering tongue
lies silent in the grave,
then in a nobler, sweeter song
I'll sing Your power to save;
I'll sing Your power to save;
I'll sing Your power to save;
then in a nobler, sweeter song
I'll sing Your power to save.

Lord, I believe You have prepared,
unworthy though I be,
for me a blood-bought, free reward,
a golden harp for me;
a golden harp for me;
a golden harp for me;
for me a blood-bought, free reward,
a golden harp for me.

It's strung and tuned for endless years
and formed by power divine
to sound in God the Father's ears
Your own most precious Name;
Your own most precious Name;
Your own most precious Name;
to sound in God the Father's ears
Your own most precious Name.

Yours is the glory! Risen, conquering Son;
endless is the victory over death You won;
angels robed in splendour rolled the stone away,
kept the folded grave clothes where Your body lay:

See! Jesus meets us, risen from the tomb,
lovingly He greets us, scatters fear and gloom.
Let the church with gladness hymns of triumph sing;
for her Lord is living, death has lost its sting:

For my pardon this I see:
nothing but the blood of Jesus;
for my cleansing, this my plea:
nothing but the blood of Jesus.

His death is my plea - my Advocate see
and hear the blood speak that has answered for me;
He purchased the grace which now I embrace;
O Father, You know He has died in my place.

Still You remain the Holy One;
in Israel's praise You are enthroned.
Our fathers put their trust in You;
they trusted, and their prayer was heard;
to You they cried; deliverance came;
they trusted and they knew no shame.

Reproached by men, by all despised,
a worm and not a man am I;
all they that see me laugh in scorn;
they shake their heads and taunting cry:
'He trusts the Lord! Let Him defend
and save Him, if He is his friend!'

Yet from the womb You brought me forth;
entrusted me to mother's breast.
From birth dependent on Your care;
from birth my God in whom I rest.
Be not far off, for grief is nigh;
with none on whom I can rely.

'Christ the Lord is risen today',
sons of men and angels say,
raise your joys and triumphs high;
sing, O heavens, and earth reply.
Love's redeeming work is done;
fought the fight the battle won;
vain the stone, the watch, the seal;
Christ has burst the gates of hell.

Lives again our glorious King;
where, O death, is now your sting?
Once He died, our souls to save;
where's your victory, O grave?
Soar we now where Christ has led,
following our exalted Head;
made like Him, like Him we rise;
ours the Cross, the grave, the skies.

Now to the King of heaven
your cheerful anthems raise;
to Him be glory given,
power, majesty and praise;
wide as He reigns His Name be sung
by every tongue in endless strains.

In all the world victorious,
He on His throne shall rest;
from age to age more glorious,
all-blessing and all-blessed;
the tide of time shall never
His covenant remove;
His Name shall stand forever,
His changeless name of love.

Glorious Lord, Yourself impart,
Light of light, from God proceeding;
open lips and ears and hearts,
help us by Your Spirit's leading;
hear the cry Your church now raises;
Lord, accept our prayers and praises.

But sinners, filled with guilty fears,
shall see His wrath prevailing;
for they shall rise, and find their tears
and sighs are unavailing;
the day of grace is past and gone;
they trembling stand before the throne
all unprepared to meet Him.

Come, Holy Ghost, our hearts inspire;
let us Your influence prove,
source of the old prophetic fire,
fountain of life and love.

Come, Holy Ghost, for moved by You
the prophets wrote and spoke;
unlock the truth, Yourself the key;
unseal the sacred Book.

Expand Your wings, celestial Dove;
brood o'er our nature's night;
on our disordered spirits move,
and let there now be light.

Gracious Spirit, dwell in me:
I myself would gracious be;
and with words that help and heal,
would Your life in mine reveal;
and with actions bold and meek,
would for Christ my Saviour speak.

Truthful Spirit, dwell in me:
I myself would truthful be;
and with wisdom kind and clear
let Your life in mine appear;
and with actions brotherly
show my Lord's sincerity.

Mighty Spirit, dwell in me:
I myself would mighty be;
mighty so as to prevail
where unaided man must fail;
always by a mighty hope
pressing onwards, bearing up.

Holy Spirit, dwell in me:
I myself would holy be;
separate from sin, I would
choose and cherish all things good;
and whatever I can be,
give to Him who made me free.

He, the mighty God, indwells us;
His to strengthen, help, empower;
His to overcome the tempter -
ours to call in danger's hour.

Your words to me are life and health;
pour strength into my soul;
enable, guide, and teach my heart
to reach its perfect goal!

Your words to me are full of joy,
of beauty, peace, and grace;
from them I learn Your blessed will,
through them I see Your face.

A glory gilds the sacred page,
majestic, like the sun;
it gives a light to every age;
it gives, but borrows none.

Your Word sheds light upon my path;
a shining light, it guides my feet;
Your righteous judgments to observe
my solemn vow I now repeat.

Look now, O God, upon our Shield;
the face of Your Anointed view;
one day within Your courts will yield
more good than thousands without You.
I'd rather stand near my God's house
than dwell in tents of wickedness.

Zion, founded on the mountains,
God, your Maker, loves you well;
He has chosen you, most precious,
He delights in you to dwell;
God's own city, God's own city,
who can all your glory tell?

Foreign lands and hostile peoples
soon shall come the Lord to know;
nations born again in Zion
shall the Lord's salvation show;
God Almighty, God Almighty,
shall on Zion strength bestow.

Among the nations He shall judge;
His judgments truth shall guide;
His sceptre shall protect the just,
and quell the sinner's pride.

We love the house of prayer;
for where Christ's people meet,
our risen Lord is there
to make our joy complete.

As sons of the day and daughters of light,
no longer we sleep like creatures of night;
for Jesus has died that with Him we may live;
by all that He gave us, we learn how to give.

One body in Christ, let all play their part:
the lazy be warned, the timid take heart;
let those who are hurt never pay back with wrong,
but serve one another: together be strong!

Let us with a dance and joyful acclaim,
with timbrel and harp, sing praise to His Name;
for God in His people His pleasure does seek;
the gift of salvation He gives to the meek.

In glory rejoice, you saints of the Lord;
with heart and with voice loud praises afford;
go forth in His service, be strong in His might
to conquer all evil and stand for the right.

The Kingdom of God is justice and joy;
for Jesus restores what sin would destroy.
God's power and glory in Jesus we know;
and here and hereafter His Kingdom shall grow.

The Kingdom of God is mercy and grace;
the captives are freed, the sinners find place,
the outcast are welcomed God's banquet to share;
and hope is awakened in place of despair.

God's Kingdom has come, the gift and the goal;
in Jesus begun, in heaven made whole.
The heirs of the Kingdom shall answer His call;
and all things cry 'Glory!'to God, All in All.

We gather together
to ask the Lord's blessing;
He chastens and hastens
His will to make known;
the wicked oppressing
now cease from distressing.
Sing praises to His Name;
He forgets not His own.

Enter His temple, ringing out His praises;
sing in thanksgiving as you come before Him;
blessing His bounty, glorify His greatness.
Praise the Almighty!

Great in His goodness is the Lord we worship;
steadfast His kindness, love that knows no ending;
faithful His Word is, changeless, everlasting.
Praise the Almighty!

Dear Shepherd of Your people, hear;
Your presence now display;
as You have given a place for prayer,
so give us hearts to pray.

Worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness;
bow down before Him, His glory proclaim;
gold of obedience and incense of lowliness
bring, and adore Him; the Lord is His Name!

Low at His feet lay your burden of carefulness;
high on His heart He will bear it for you;
comfort your sorrows, and answer your prayerfulness,
guiding your steps in His way, which is true.

Worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness;
bow down before Him, His glory proclaim;
gold of obedience and incense of lowliness
bring, and adore Him; the Lord is His Name!

Be still and know that I am God;
be still and know that I am God;
be still and know that I am God.

Lord, dismiss us with Your blessing;
fill our hearts with joy and peace;
let us each, Your love possessing,
triumph in redeeming grace.
O refresh us, O refresh us,
travelling thro' this wilderness.

Grant us Your peace Lord, through the coming night;
turn now for us its darkness into light;
from harm and danger keep us Lord, we pray,
until at last we reach Your endless day.

Grant us Your peace throughout our earthly life;
peace to Your church from error and from strife;
peace to our land, the fruit of truth and love;
peace in each heart, Your Spirit from above:

Your peace in sorrow, balm of every pain;
Your peace in death, the hope to rise again;
then when Your voice shall bid our conflict cease,
call us, O Lord, to Your eternal peace.

Let Zion's time of favour come;
O bring the tribes of Israel home;
and let our wondering eyes behold
gentiles and Jews in Jesus' fold.

Almighty God, Your grace display
in every land and every tongue;
let hostile powers before You fall,
and crown the Saviour Lord of all.

Lord, as the day begins
lift up our hearts in praise;
take from us all our sins,
guard us in all our ways;
our ev'ry step direct and guide
that Christ in all be glorified!

Christ be in work and skill,
serving each other's need;
Christ be in thought and will,
Christ be in word and deed;
our minds be set on things above
in joy and peace, in faith and love.

Grant us the Spirit's strength,
teach us to walk His way;
so bring us all at length
safe to the close of day:
from hour to hour sustain and bless,
and let our song be thankfulness.

Verse 3:
The Lord God bless you from above,
from Zion in His boundless love,
our God, who heav'n and earth has made;
blest be His great and holy Name.

If in the night I sleepless lie,
my mind with heavenly thoughts supply;
let no dark dreams disturb my rest,
no powers of evil me molest.

Baptise this child with needed grace;
set him apart before Your face;
that he may choose to run the race
with Christ the Lord.

Our children, Lord, in faith and prayer,
we now devote to You;
let them Your covenant mercies share,
and Your salvation know.

For the bread and for the wine,
for the pledge that seals Him mine;
for the words of love divine,
we give You thanks, O Lord.

For that coming here foretold,
for that day to us unknown,
for the glory and the throne,
we give You thanks, O Lord.

Look, Father, look on His anointed face,
and only look on us as found in Him;
look not on our misusings of Your grace,
our prayer so feeble and our faith so dim;
for, set between our sins and their reward,
we see the cross of Christ Your Son, our Lord.

And so we come: O draw us to Your feet,
most patient Saviour, who can love us still;
and by this food, so awesome and so sweet,
deliver us from every touch of ill;
for Your glad service, Master, set us free,
and make us Lord what You would have us be.

Then in His hands the cup He raised,
and God again He thanked and praised;
while kindness in His actions showed,
and from His lips salvation flowed.

Love divine first drew us to You,
in our sin and need;
for our sin, in deep compassion,
You did bleed.

Mine is the sin, but Yours the righteousness;
mine is the guilt, but Yours the cleansing blood;
here is my robe, my refuge, and my peace:
Your blood, Your righteousness, O Lord my God.

Lord You the strength to workers' arms impart;
from You the skilled musician's pleasing art,
the grace of poet's pen or painter's hand
to teach the loveliness of sea and land.

Hark! Hark! The trump of jubilee
proclaims to every nation,
from pole to pole, by land and sea,
glad tidings of salvation;
as nearer draws the day of doom,
while still the battle rages,
the heavenly dayspring through the gloom,
breaks on the night of ages.

Still on and on the anthems spread,
of hallelujah voices;
in concert with the holy dead,
the warrior church rejoices;
their snow-white robes are washed in blood,
their golden harps are ringing;
earth and the Paradise of God
one triumph song are singing.

Go where the needs are great,
bearing the Word of grace;
aid, in the Name of Christ
people of every race.
The sick ones heal, the hungry feed;
for His sake help them in their need.

Think once again, He's with us today;
heed now His blest commands, and obey;
hear now His accents tenderly say:
'Will you, my children, come?'

Sing them over again to me:
wonderful words of life;
let me more of their beauty see,
wonderful words of life.
Words of life and beauty,
teach me faith and duty:

Take His easy yoke and wear it;
love will make obedience sweet;
Christ will give you strength to bear it,
while His wisdom guides your feet
safe to glory, safe to glory,
where His ransomed captives meet.

In Christ is Adam's ransom met,
earth, by His cross, is holy ground;
Eden indeed is with us yet;
in Christ are life and freedom found!

Chorus
I am coming, Lord;
at Your offer free;
wash me, cleanse me, in the blood
that flowed on Calvary.

Jesus, the Saviour, this Gospel to tell
joyfully came;
came with the helpless and hopeless to dwell,
sharing their sorrow and shame;
seeking the lost, saving,
redeeming at measureless cost.

Jesus is seeking the wanderers yet;
why do they roam?
Love only waits to forgive and forget;
home, weary wanderer, home!
Wonderful love dwells in the heart
of the Father above.

If I come to Jesus,
He will hear my prayer;
He will love me dearly;
He my sins did bear.

God, be merciful to me,
on Your grace I rest my plea;
plenteous in compassion, Lord,
mercy for my sins afford;
wash me, make me pure within,
cleanse, O cleanse me from my sin.

My transgressions I confess,
grief and guilt my soul oppress;
I have sinned against Your grace
and provoked You to Your face;
I confess Your judgment just,
speechless, I Your mercy trust.

Long my imprisoned spirit lay,
fast bound in sin and nature's night:
Your sunrise turned that night to day;
I woke, the dungeon flamed with light.
My chains fell off, Your voice I knew;
I rose, went out and followed You!
My chains fell off, Your voice I knew;
I rose, went out and followed You!

My stony heart to flesh convert,
my inbred sin from me remove;
apply Your blood to all my heart,
and melt it by Your dying love;
this rebel heart by love subdue,
O make it soft and make it new.

Jesus, lover of my soul,
let me to Your presence fly,
while the gath'ring waters roll,
while the tempest still is high.
Hide me, O my Saviour, hide,
till the storms of life are past;
safe into the haven, guide,
and receive my soul at last.

Not what I am, O Lord, but what You are;
that, that alone can make me feel secure;
Your love, not mine, bids fear and doubt depart,
untangles worries that can choke the heart.

From what I know of You, my Lord and God,
my soul is filled with peace, my lips with song;
You are my health, my joy, my staff, my rod;
leaning on You, in weakness I am strong.

More of Yourself Lord, show me hour by hour;
more of Your glory, O my God and Lord;
more of Yourself in all Your grace and power;
more of Your love and truth, Incarnate Word.

I lay my wants on Jesus;
all fullness dwells in Him;
He heals all my diseases,
and He my soul redeems.
I lay my griefs on Jesus,
my burdens, and my cares;
He from them all releases,
He all my sorrows shares.

Rock of Ages, cleft for me,
hide me now, my refuge be;
let the water and the blood
from Your wounded side which flowed,
be for sin the double cure,
cleanse me from its guilt and power.

Nothing in my hand I bring,
simply to Your cross I cling;
naked, come to You for dress,
helpless, look to You for grace;
stained by sin, to You I cry:
'Wash me, Saviour, or I die!'

I am trusting You for pardon,
at Your feet I bow;
for Your grace and tender mercy,
trusting now.

Jesus my Lord will love me forever,
from Him no pow'r of evil can sever;
He gave His life to ransom my soul,
now I belong to Him;

High is the rank we now possess;
but higher we shall rise;
though what we shall hereafter be
is hid from mortal eyes.

Our souls, we know, when He appears,
shall bear His image bright;
for all His glory, full disclosed,
shall open to our sight.

Let Your love my heart inflame;
keep Your fear before my sight;
be Your praise my highest goal;
be Your smile my chief delight,
be Your smile my chief delight.

Thus, O thus, an entrance give
to the land of endless joy;
having known that Christ is life,
let me know to die is gain,
let me know to die is gain.

Love God with all your soul and strength,
with all your heart and mind;
and love your neighbour as yourself;
be faithful, just and kind.

Breathe through the heats of our desire
Your coolness and Your balm;
let sense be dumb, let flesh retire,
speak through the earthquake, wind and fire,
O still, small voice of calm,
O still, small voice of calm!

O search me, Lord, and prove me now;
Your mercy I adore;
I choose Your truth to be my guide,
and sinful ways abhor.

But we never can prove
the delights of His love
until all on the altar we lay;
for the favour He shows,
and the joy He bestows,
are for those who will trust and obey.

Consecrate me now to Your service Lord,
by the power of grace divine;
let my soul look up with a steadfast hope,
and my will be thus refined.

I have but myself to give:
let me to Your glory live;
let me follow day by day,
as You lead me in Your way.

Walk in the light: and yours shall be
a path, though thorny, bright;
for God, by grace, shall dwell in you,
and God Himself is Light.

His is the strength by which I live;
His risen life I share;
and if I want to rise with Him
I suffer with Him here.

Lord, turn away my feared reproach;
forgive my sins of youth,
since for Your precepts I have longed;
renew me in Your truth.

Finish then Your new creation;:
pure and sinless let us be;
let us see Your great salvation,
perfect in eternity;
changed from glory into glory
till in heav'n we take our place,
there to cast our crowns before You,
lost in wonder, love and praise!

The Lord, who left the heaven's
our life and peace to bring;
to dwell in lowliness with us,
our pattern and our King;

Do no sinful action;
speak no angry word;
you belong to Jesus,
children of the Lord.

Lord You can help when earthly armour fails us;
Lord, You can save when deadly sin assails us;
You, O Lord Christ, alone, will never fail us,
grant us Your peace, Lord.

Peace in our hearts, our evil thoughts assuaging;
peace in Your church where brothers are engaging;
peace, when the world its busy war is waging:
calm Your foes' raging.

Chosen to be soldiers
in an alien land,
chosen, called, and faithful,
for our Captain's band,
in the service royal
let us not grow cold;
let us be right loyal,
noble, true, and bold.

March on, my soul, with strength,
march forward, void of fear;
He who has led will lead,
while year succeeds to year;
and as you travel on your way,
His hand shall hold you day by day.

March on, my soul, with strength,
in ease you dare not dwell;
high duty calls you forth;
then up, and quit you well!
Take up your cross, take up your sword,
and fight the battles of your Lord!

Now we arise and upright stand,
while they, subdued and helpless, fall;
O Lord God, save us by Your hand;
King, give answer when we call.

Stand up, stand up for Jesus,
the trumpet-call obey;
then join the mighty conflict
in this His glorious day.
Be strong in faith and serve Him
against unnumbered foes;
let courage rise with danger,
and strength to strength oppose.

Go labour on: spend and be spent,
your joy to do the Father's will;
it is the way the Master went;
should not the servant tread it still?

Go, labour on while it is day:
the world's dark night is hastening on;
speed, speed your work; cast sloth away;
it is not thus that souls are won.

Toil on, and in your toil rejoice;
for toil comes rest, for exile home;
soon shall you hear the Bridegroom's voice,
the midnight peal: 'Behold, I come!'

Jesus bids us shine, first of all for Him;
well He sees and knows it, if our light is dim;
He looks down from heaven, to see us shine:
you in your small corner, and I in mine.

Chorus
Rescue the perishing, care for the dying;
Jesus is merciful, Jesus will save.

Jesus, Master, I am Yours:
keep me faithful keep me near;
let Your presence shine in me,
all my homeward way to cheer.
Jesus, at Your feet I fall,
dear Lord, be my All in All.

Pour out Your Spirit from on high;
Lord, Your ordain'd servants bless;
graces and gifts to each supply,
and clothe them with Your righteousness.

To watch and pray, and never faint;
by day and night strict guard to keep;
to warn the sinner, cheer the saint,
nourish Your lambs and feed Your sheep.

Restrain your lips from speaking wrong,
from lying speech depart,
from evil turn and do the good,
seek peace with all your heart.

For God's eyes are upon the just,
He listens to their cry;
against the wicked God remains;
their very name shall die.

Father, lead me day by day,
always in Your own wise way;
teach me to be pure and true;
show me what I ought to do.

When in danger, make me brave;
make me know that You can save;
keep me safe by Your dear side,
let me in Your love abide.

Teach me the way that I should go;
I lift my soul to You;
for refuge from my cruel foe
I flee, O Lord, to You.

Preserve my sinking soul, I pray,
from tides of hatred save;
let not the waters overflow,
redeem me from the grave.

All day I groaned in silence,
my body was dismayed;
as in a drought I thirsted;
Your hand was on me laid.
But then I owned my trespass,
my guilt hid not from You;
I made to God confession,
and You my guilt removed.

In many seeing it, fear will come;
they then will trust in the Lord;
and he is happy who hopes in the Lord
who will not be led astray.
Your wondrous deeds and thoughts to us
are multiplied, O my God;
they number more than we can proclaim
Lord! None compares with You!

I love the Lord, His strength is mine;
He is my God, I trust His grace;
my fortress high, my shield divine,
my Saviour and my hiding place.

From bondage great He set me free,
He saved the man of His delight;
for good the Lord rewarded me,
and gave me favour in His sight.

The Lord is rich and merciful;
the Lord is very kind;
O come to Him, come now to Him,
with a believing mind.
His blessings, they shall strengthen you,
like flowing waters cool;
and He shall for your spirit be
a fountain ever full.

You are coming to a King;
large petitions with you bring;
for His grace and power are such,
none can ever ask too much.

With my burden I begin:
Lord, remove this load of sin;
let Your blood, for sinners spilt,
set my conscience free from guilt.

Lord, in You my peace I find;
take possession of my mind;
there Your blood-bought right maintain,
and without a rival reign.

Lead us in Your way, make us strong;
when temptations come make us strong;
save us from all sin, keep us strong.
O Lord, hear our prayer.

Lord, take my life, my sinful soul refine;
fill my poor heart with Your great love divine.
Take all my will, my passion, self and pride;
I now surrender, Lord, in me abide.

Jesus, my Lord, my God, my all;
hear me, O Saviour, when I call;
hear me, and from Your dwelling-place,
pour down the riches of Your grace.
Jesus, my Lord, whom I adore,
help me to love You more and more.

Lord of all being, I give You my all;
if I ever disown You, I stumble and fall;
but, led in Your service Your Word to obey,
I'll walk in Your freedom to the end of the way.

Behold, the sparrow searches out
a house wherein to rest;
the swallow also for herself
has deftly built a nest;

Jesus is our Shepherd, well we know His voice;
how its gentlest whisper makes our hearts rejoice!
Even when He chides us tender is its tone;
none but He shall guide us; we are His alone.

Support me in the strenuous race
and do not let my footsteps stray;
still strengthen me with heavenly grace
to persevere upon Your way;
to serve You, Lord, with all my might
and make Your glory my delight.

On the good and faithful God has set His love;
when they call He sends them blessings from above.
Stand in awe and sin not, bid your heart be still;
through the hours of darkness think upon His will.

God will not let His saints be moved;
protected they shall be,
foes all cut off and sin reproved;
and God's salvation see.

O Lord, to You I cry;
You are my rock and trust;
do not be silent, lest I die
and slumber in the dust.

Now put your trust in God,
in duty's path go on;
walk in His strength with faith and hope,
so shall your work be done.
Throw to the winds your fears;
hope, and be undismayed;
God hears your sighs and counts your tears,
God shall lift up your head.

Master, speak, for I am listening,
waiting for Your gracious Word,
longing for Your tender calling;
Master, let it now be heard.
I am waiting Lord, to see;
what You have to say to me.

Master, speak, though I am lowly
let me not unheard depart;
Master speak and make me holy -
that's the longing of my heart.
Knowing well my deepest need;
speak, and make me blest indeed.

My heart is weak and poor
until it master find;
it has no spring of action sure;
it varies with the wind.
It cannot feely move
unless You should restrain;
enslave it with Your matchless love,
and deathless it shall reign.

My power is faint and low
till I have learned to serve;
it wants the needed fire to glow,
it wants the breeze to nerve;
it cannot drive the world
until itself be driven;
its flag can only be unfurled
when You shall breathe from heaven.

Have Your own way, Lord,
have Your own way;
wounded and weary, help me, I pray.
Power, all power, surely is Yours;
touch me and heal me, Saviour and Lord.

I would live always in the light;
I would work always for the right;
I would serve You with all my might;
therefore, to You I come.

Take me now, Lord Jesus, take me;
may my life, Lord Jesus, shine,
Your devoted servant make me;
fill my soul with love divine.

I am Yours, O Lord, forever,
to Your service set apart;
Saviour may I leave You never;
seal Your image on my heart.

My times are in Your hand;
my God, I wish them there;
my life, my friends, my soul, I leave
entirely to Your care.

Lord You will keep him in perfect peace;
Lord You will keep him in perfect peace;
Lord You will keep him in perfect peace;
whose mind is stayed on You.

Marvel not that I say unto you;
marvel not that I say unto you;
marvel not that I say unto you;
you must be born again.

Though your sins as scarlet be;
though your sins as scarlet be;
though your sins as scarlet be;
they shall be white as snow.

If the Son shall set you free,
if the Son shall set you free,
if the Son shall set you free,
You shall be free indeed.

In heavenly love abiding,
no change my heart shall fear:
and safe is such confiding,
for nothing changes here:
the storm may roar around me,
my heart may low be laid;
my Father's arms surround me;
how can I be afraid?

Like a river glorious is God's perfect peace,
over all victorious, in its bright increase;
perfect, yet still flowing fuller every day;
perfect, yet still growing deeper all the way.

Take, my soul, your full salvation;
rise o'er sin, and fear, and care;
joy to find in every station
something still to do or bear.
Think what Spirit dwells within you,
what a Father's smile is yours,
what your Saviour did to win you;
child of heaven, should you despair?

O for a faith that will not shrink,
though pressed by many a foe;
that will not tremble on the brink
of poverty or woe;

that will not murmur or complain
beneath the chastening rod;
but in the hour of grief or pain
can lean upon its God;

a faith that shines more bright and clear
when tempests rage without;
that when in danger knows no fear,
in darkness feels no doubt;

Worthy the Lamb that died, they cry,
to be exalted thus;
worthy the Lamb, let earth reply;
for He was slain for us.

For the might of Your arm we bless You,
our God, our fathers' God;
You have kept Your pilgrim people
by the strength of Your staff and rod;
You have called us to the journey
which faithless feet ne'er trod:
for the might of Your arm we bless You,
our God, our fathers' God.

For the love of Christ constraining,
that bound their hearts as one;
for the faith in truth and freedom
in which their work was done;
for the peace of God's evangel
wherewith their feet were shod:
for the might of Your arm we bless You,
our God, our fathers' God.

We are watchers of a beacon
whose light must never die;
we are guardians of an altar
that shows You ever nigh;
we are children of Your freemen
who rest beneath the sod:
for the might of Your arm we bless You,
our God, our fathers' God.

Let your heart be tender and your vision clear,
see mankind as God sees, serve Him far and near;
let Your heart be broken by a brother's pain,
share your rich resources, give and give again.

Except You build it, Father,
the house is built in vain;
except You bless it, Saviour,
the joy will turn to pain:
but none can break the union
of hearts in You made one;
and love Your Spirit hallows
is endless love begun.

O Trinity of love and power,
preserve their lives in danger's hour;
from rock and tempest, flood and flame,
protect them by Your Holy Name.
Thus evermore with thanks shall we
give praise from air and land and sea.

